g, if present, likely occurs only on a smaller scale,\nleading to an accumulation of magnetic flux and thus efficient magnetic braking\nin the inner envelope. However, because of our limited angular resolution, we\ncannot rule out a significant ambipolar drift only in the midplane of the\ninfalling envelope. Future observations with higher angular resolutions (~0.1\")\nare needed to examine this possibility and ambipolar diffusion on a smaller\nscale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Mar 2018 04:29:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-18"}
